1
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 31=

3
00:01:38,180 --> 00:01:42,620
(Wind and Rainbow Choir
A Charity Performance at East Suburb)

4
00:01:42,890 --> 00:01:44,480
♪Young friends♪

5
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,970
♪Let's gather here today♪

6
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:49,330
♪Drifting down the stream,
a warm breeze gently blows♪

7
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:51,560
♪The flowers bloom, the birds sing♪

8
00:01:51,666 --> 00:01:53,450
♪The beauty of spring
takes our breath away♪

9
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:56,330
♪With joyful songs and laughter,
we soar through colorful skies♪

10
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:58,250
♪Dear friends♪

11
00:01:58,450 --> 00:02:00,450
♪Who does this wonderful
springtime belong to♪

12
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:02,280
♪It belongs to me♪

13
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:03,890
♪It belongs to you♪

14
00:02:04,050 --> 00:02:08,290
♪It belongs to us,
the new generation of the 1980s♪

15
00:02:08,570 --> 00:02:18,050
♪The new generation of the 1980s♪

16
00:02:18,050 --> 00:02:18,480
Bravo!

17
00:02:28,010 --> 00:02:28,290
Lina.

18
00:02:28,326 --> 00:02:29,050
(Joy Academy)

19
00:02:29,050 --> 00:02:31,044
This is a gift from Joy Academy
for our investors.

20
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:33,170
Whole grains? So practical.

21
00:02:33,170 --> 00:02:33,800
It's good.

22
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,290
Bai, that training program
you recommended...

23
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:37,680
I actually liked it.

24
00:02:38,066 --> 00:02:39,520
I'll transfer the course fee to you.

25
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:40,760
What?

26
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,920
No need. It's on me.

27
00:02:46,850 --> 00:02:48,480
Oh, you're so generous.

28
00:02:49,450 --> 00:02:51,080
People usually treat
each other to meals,

29
00:02:51,111 --> 00:02:53,888
but I've never heard of treating
someone to a training course.

30
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:55,050
Tell you what,

31
00:02:55,088 --> 00:02:56,170
once I start making money,

32
00:02:56,222 --> 00:02:57,010
I'll give you a cut.

33
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:59,400
And if you ever have
a money-making opportunity,

34
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,666
don't forget to loop me in too.

35
00:03:00,666 --> 00:03:01,410
Of course I will.

36
00:03:02,890 --> 00:03:03,170
Lina,

37
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,890
this project actually has great returns.

38
00:03:06,130 --> 00:03:08,410
Last quarter it shot up over 20%.

39
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,644
You should really think
about investing a little.

40
00:03:14,044 --> 00:03:16,088
I'm broke, so I'll just
watch from the sidelines.

41
00:03:16,444 --> 00:03:17,050
That's okay.

42
00:03:19,610 --> 00:03:20,450
Alright then. Thanks!

43
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:20,850
Bye.

44
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:21,570
Bye.

45
00:03:43,466 --> 00:03:44,640
What are you looking for?

46
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,640
A red folder.

47
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,080
It...

48
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:47,977
It was just here.

49
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:49,850
I remember leaving it here,
so where did it go?

50
00:03:49,850 --> 00:03:50,570
You mean that one?

51
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:56,239
How did it end up over there?

52
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,330
I looked there earlier.

53
00:03:57,330 --> 00:03:58,400
I didn't see it at all.

54
00:03:58,644 --> 00:04:01,240
You men always dreaming big,
chasing poetry and faraway places,

55
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,890
and ignoring what's right
in front of you.

56
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,010
That Joy Academy project

57
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:06,480
is an R5-level financial product.

58
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:07,850
High risk to your principal.

59
00:04:07,890 --> 00:04:08,570
Stay out of it.

60
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:10,200
You're only looking at the risks.

61
00:04:10,222 --> 00:04:11,955
Why don't you take a look
at the returns too?

62
00:04:12,610 --> 00:04:14,240
You should stay away from Bai.

63
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:17,120
Why are you talking about him like that?

64
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,970
He's a legit graduate
from a top-tier university.

65
00:04:18,977 --> 00:04:19,777
He knows his stuff.

66
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:21,800
No legit financial adviser

67
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,990
goes around handing out gifts
to clients for no reason.

68
00:04:24,050 --> 00:04:25,290
So you did see me earlier.

69
00:04:26,090 --> 00:04:27,120
You didn't even say hi.

70
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,000
How polite of you.

71
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:30,320
I was in a rush to grab the folder.

72
00:04:30,610 --> 00:04:32,290
So, you just pretended I was invisible?

73
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:34,090
You may not think much of me,

74
00:04:34,610 --> 00:04:36,050
but plenty of other people do.

75
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,680
Don't assume your standards

76
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,240
are like official certifications,

77
00:04:39,266 --> 00:04:41,340
that without your stamp of approval,
I don't count.

78
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:42,770
I'm not saying you're wrong.

79
00:04:42,770 --> 00:04:45,120
I'm just saying,
be careful with your investments.

80
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:47,210
I majored in accounting too, okay?

81
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:47,800
Besides,

82
00:04:48,090 --> 00:04:49,480
you've lost all our money.

83
00:04:49,488 --> 00:04:51,210
What can I even invest with?

84
00:04:52,410 --> 00:04:52,650
Right.

85
00:04:53,050 --> 00:04:54,120
I lost our money.

86
00:04:54,155 --> 00:04:55,822
And I'm doing my best to earn it back.

87
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:04,610
Shen Qing, over here.

88
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,050
Sorry.

89
00:05:07,222 --> 00:05:08,780
I set the meeting, yet I showed up late.

90
00:05:09,050 --> 00:05:09,530
It's fine.

91
00:05:09,577 --> 00:05:11,000
Gave me a chance to take a break.

92
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,360
What are you reading?

93
00:05:12,410 --> 00:05:14,530
Just brushing up on the past
to learn something new.

94
00:05:14,955 --> 00:05:15,880
It's from the café.

95
00:05:15,888 --> 00:05:17,088
Figured I'd flip through it.

96
00:05:17,688 --> 00:05:19,290
I feel like a chameleon these days.

97
00:05:20,177 --> 00:05:22,844
Constantly reading people's expressions,
and adjusting my words.

98
00:05:22,850 --> 00:05:24,244
Always bending with the wind.

99
00:05:24,970 --> 00:05:26,880
So what color are you today?

100
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:30,244
My true colors.

101
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,440
Actually,

102
00:05:43,666 --> 00:05:46,155
I came here today
to lay everything on the table.

103
00:05:51,850 --> 00:05:53,680
This is last month's financial report.

104
00:05:54,970 --> 00:05:56,240
Admin salaries have been cut.

105
00:05:56,850 --> 00:05:59,360
R&D salaries were delayed.

106
00:06:01,822 --> 00:06:03,680
Here's the Phase 3
clinical trial report.

107
00:06:06,730 --> 00:06:08,210
This is the company's loan agreement.

108
00:06:14,466 --> 00:06:17,488
And this is a record of every
executive's personal contributions.

109
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:21,780
(RF Pharmaceuticals -
Internal Fundraising Record)

110
00:06:23,644 --> 00:06:25,600
RF Pharmaceuticals
is in serious trouble.

111
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,480
We've got a loan due tomorrow,

112
00:06:29,650 --> 00:06:31,410
and we're out of cash.

113
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,666
If the next round of funding
doesn't come through,

114
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,120
we're done for.

115
00:06:38,577 --> 00:06:40,170
Showing these confidential documents

116
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:42,320
to investors

117
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,290
is humiliating.

118
00:06:45,650 --> 00:06:47,170
But in times like this,

119
00:06:47,933 --> 00:06:49,977
we don't have the luxury of saving face.

120
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:53,530
Ice, I know you've done a lot to help.

121
00:06:54,911 --> 00:06:56,500
And it's perfectly reasonable for a fund

122
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:59,210
to be cautious about risk.

123
00:06:59,290 --> 00:06:59,680
But...

124
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,610
As an investor,

125
00:07:01,666 --> 00:07:04,333
we should have the guts
to take risks with the project.

126
00:07:05,888 --> 00:07:08,222
I'll go back and renegotiate
with the company.

127
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:10,000
Shen Qing,

128
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,000
please give me

129
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:14,800
a little more time before tomorrow.

130
00:07:19,050 --> 00:07:22,290
♪From this day on♪

131
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,850
♪May we never forget♪

132
00:07:26,290 --> 00:07:38,880
♪Those nights
on the outskirts of Moscow♪

133
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:45,170
Wind and Rainbow Choir,

134
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,480
this concludes our performance.

135
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,410
Bravo!

136
00:07:55,088 --> 00:07:56,577
If Heibao tries to come after him,

137
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,800
stall him, and keep him busy.

138
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:58,680
Got it.

139
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:00,560
Dismissed!

140
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:02,680
The weather's pretty nice today.

141
00:08:02,970 --> 00:08:04,880
Let's go to the back hill
to take some photos.

142
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:05,480
Mr. Shen.

143
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:05,850
Yes?

144
00:08:05,911 --> 00:08:07,290
Can you help us take some pictures?

145
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,050
Sure.

146
00:08:08,170 --> 00:08:08,680
Come again!

147
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,120
Let's go!

148
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:10,680
Let's go.

149
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,610
Hello there.

150
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,170
Bye.

151
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:13,480
Do you like singing too?

152
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:14,050
No,

153
00:08:14,610 --> 00:08:15,440
I don't.

154
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:16,360
I'm tone-deaf.

155
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,050
Look,

156
00:08:18,290 --> 00:08:19,050
don't be shy now.

157
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:20,770
Tone-deaf is not a problem.

158
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,240
Let's go then.

159
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,240
I bet

160
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:28,680
when you were younger,

161
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,610
you probably didn't dare

162
00:08:31,770 --> 00:08:32,600
to sing out loud.

163
00:08:32,770 --> 00:08:35,370
And now you just assume
you're tone-deaf.

164
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,600
You know what,

165
00:08:36,770 --> 00:08:37,960
we've got a piano here.

166
00:08:38,066 --> 00:08:40,333
You could try some sight-singing
and ear training.

167
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:40,840
I think

168
00:08:41,010 --> 00:08:42,680
- you'd do just fine.
- I've tried it.

169
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,770
I've tried. Doesn't work.

170
00:08:44,177 --> 00:08:44,560
What...

171
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,440
Really?

172
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:46,840
Don't go!

173
00:08:50,050 --> 00:08:50,920
Li Heibao is here.

174
00:08:52,755 --> 00:08:54,444
Does that make you feel confused?

175
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:56,010
A little.

176
00:08:56,644 --> 00:08:58,010
Actually, not confused,

177
00:08:58,010 --> 00:08:59,370
just kind of unsettled.

178
00:08:59,955 --> 00:09:02,050
I mean, we were together
for almost three years.

179
00:09:02,666 --> 00:09:04,320
If it hadn't been for his daughter...

180
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,050
Back then,

181
00:09:07,170 --> 00:09:09,200
he promised he'd win me a gold medal.

182
00:09:09,370 --> 00:09:11,080
And look, he got it.

183
00:09:11,890 --> 00:09:13,410
But now we're not together anymore.

184
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,600
Don't worry.
I'll appreciate the present.

185
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:22,010
Mr. Shen!

186
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,840
Finally caught up with you two.

187
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,200
Let's take this path.

188
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,080
The other one is a bit tricky to walk.

189
00:09:29,530 --> 00:09:31,200
Yes, too many steps over there.

190
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,770
Let's stick to the flat road.

191
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:33,560
Hello, Mr. Shen!

192
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:35,050
Don't fall behind. Keep up!

193
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:35,840
Come on.

194
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:36,490
Let's go.

195
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:37,080
Let's go.

196
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,130
Keep going.

197
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,720
Shen just sent a message.

198
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,410
They went down that path.

199
00:09:45,444 --> 00:09:47,190
He said we should take
this one to catch up.

200
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:47,680
Excuse me.

201
00:09:51,370 --> 00:09:52,200
Ah, it's you two.

202
00:09:55,170 --> 00:09:56,680
Could you tell me which way

203
00:09:57,410 --> 00:09:58,170
did Le Shuishan go?

204
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:02,960
Thank you.

205
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:09,720
Ding,

206
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,200
look at you.

207
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,800
You're sharper than I thought!

208
00:10:14,770 --> 00:10:15,840
Guai guai long di dong.

209
00:10:16,177 --> 00:10:17,680
Chives stir-fried with green onions.

210
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,320
He's in such great shape.

211
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:21,600
I'd better call Shen now.

212
00:10:24,410 --> 00:10:24,890
Shen,

213
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,650
Li Heibao's catching up.

214
00:10:26,770 --> 00:10:27,920
The guy's in great shape.

215
00:10:28,130 --> 00:10:29,650
He runs like the wind.

216
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,170
Ding pointed him down the wrong path.

217
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,720
You'd better be ready.

218
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,770
Knowledge is power,

219
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,530
but physical strength is power too.

220
00:10:37,977 --> 00:10:39,622
This is as much as we can do to help.

221
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:40,560
Good luck!

222
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,170
Alright.

223
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:43,490
Alright.

224
00:11:00,370 --> 00:11:01,440
Alright, ladies,

225
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,650
strike those beautiful poses!

226
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,200
Give me a little more energy!

227
00:11:04,410 --> 00:11:05,250
Say one, two, three.

228
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,130
Yes, yes.

229
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,010
One,

230
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:07,650
two,

231
00:11:08,050 --> 00:11:09,720
three.

232
00:11:26,530 --> 00:11:27,650
Perfect, looks great!

233
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:28,909
We need one from higher up too.

234
00:11:28,910 --> 00:11:31,400
A top-down shot so we can
get the city in the background, right?

235
00:11:31,422 --> 00:11:31,844
Yes.

236
00:11:31,844 --> 00:11:33,840
Okay. You guys get into position.
I'm heading up.

237
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:34,170
Okay.

238
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,650
Where should I stand?

239
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:36,250
Stand here.

240
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:37,050
Here.

241
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:40,920
Mr. Shen, are you okay?

242
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:41,890
Are you okay?

243
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,050
What's wrong?

244
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:46,080
I'm fine.

245
00:11:46,266 --> 00:11:47,790
I'm going to climb up a little higher.

246
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,000
Think about your poses.

247
00:11:49,022 --> 00:11:50,088
I'll take a bunch of shots.

248
00:11:50,088 --> 00:11:51,600
Mr. Shen is so thoughtful.

249
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,560
So?

250
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:54,130
He's such a sweetheart.

251
00:11:54,170 --> 00:11:55,560
Mr. Shen is just the best.

252
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:57,490
I think that's high enough!

253
00:11:57,511 --> 00:11:58,490
He can a few extra shots.

254
00:11:58,490 --> 00:11:59,130
Yes.

255
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:01,200
Got the perfect spot!

256
00:12:01,755 --> 00:12:02,290
Here we go.

257
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:02,650
Okay.

258
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:03,290
Okay.

259
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:03,720
Ready?

260
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:04,600
Ladies,

261
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:06,410
one, two, three.

262
00:12:06,890 --> 00:12:07,370
Okay!

263
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,490
Check the photos.

264
00:12:09,490 --> 00:12:09,960
Look.

265
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:10,720
Here.

266
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,200
We look so nice.

267
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:16,050
This turned out great.

268
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:18,530
Look. You can even see the
whole background from here.

269
00:12:18,770 --> 00:12:19,170
Yes.

270
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:20,770
It's all thanks

271
00:12:21,490 --> 00:12:22,720
to my keen eye for details.

272
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:24,010
Look,

273
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,840
I captured your best smile

274
00:12:26,010 --> 00:12:26,770
in the shot.

275
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,080
Geez,

276
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,050
those ladies aren't cool.

277
00:12:33,050 --> 00:12:34,530
They didn't even wait for us.

278
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:45,200
Mr. Shen, are you okay?

279
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:46,130
I'm fine.

280
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:47,050
Did you hurt your back?

281
00:12:47,050 --> 00:12:47,410
No.

282
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:49,050
Let me carry you.

283
00:12:49,130 --> 00:12:49,720
It's fine.

284
00:12:49,777 --> 00:12:50,600
No, I have to try.

